The paper deals with submodular maximization, which is a fundamental problem in theoretical computer science and optimization. The use of matroid and packing constraints is also a common technique in this area. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of adaptive and parallel algorithms, which are topics in cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
